532
00:21:10,519 --> 00:21:11,679
and this was their estate.

533
00:21:12,947 --> 00:21:14,187
And so of course they knew all the secrets

534
00:21:14,227 --> 00:21:15,407
and they were all members and stuff.

535
00:21:15,547 --> 00:21:18,028
So to solve this problem and to signal a sense of mystery

536
00:21:18,068 --> 00:21:20,289
right off the bat, we just opened the game with this quote,

537
00:21:20,329 --> 00:21:21,969
which had been a tagline from our website.

538
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:25,190
So there's lots more in the game,

539
00:21:25,410 --> 00:21:28,631
but I'm gonna focus on just a few most noteworthy moments.

540
00:21:30,231 --> 00:21:31,792
This scene worked great at conveying

541
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:33,392
that someone was spying on DV

542
00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:35,453
and it introduced a mystery of who the spy was

543
00:21:35,513 --> 00:21:36,853
at a time that worked well for the story.

544
00:21:37,513 --> 00:21:39,934
Many players cite this as one of their favorite moments

545
00:21:40,694 --> 00:21:41,855
and it wasn't one of the anchor moments.

546
00:21:42,285 --> 00:21:46,006
Usually those are the ones that work best since they're originally conceived as being visually strong.

547
00:21:46,466 --> 00:21:49,948
I think this one works because the reveal is exciting, because you're just in that room.

